narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Directed Research is the perfect opportunity to explore your research interests as they connect to cognitive science.

This was an incredible opportunity and one of the most valuable courses I've taken at Yale (to the extent you can call it a course). If you have a good professor to work with, I would absolutely do Directed Research.
A good thing to sign up for so that you can get another credit out of the way if you're already planning on doing research during the semester.
